   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>From the App Launcher, find and open the Power CLM app. You can perform the same action in Power CPQ app as well. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the<uicontrol> Data Mappings</uicontrol> tab from the navigation bar.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter the <uicontrol>Data Mapping Name</uicontrol>. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select <uicontrol>Default Data Mapping</uicontrol> check box.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Under the <uicontrol>Fields Mapping</uicontrol> section, click <uicontrol>Add Mapping</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Selected Object</uicontrol> link and select <uicontrol>Agreement</uicontrol> from the picklist menu.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Select</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Under the <uicontrol>File Mapping</uicontrol> section, click <uicontrol>Add
                  Mapping</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>From <uicontrol>Which File to Add?</uicontrol> picklist menu, select <uicontrol>Audit Trail</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>
               <p>For more information on sending a document for eSignature, refer
                     <uicontrol>Sending for eSignature </uicontrol>topic in <uicontrol>Adobe Sign
                     Services on Salesforce User Guide</uicontrol>.</p>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
